SIMPLE: eternity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eternity
<hw>E*ter"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Eternities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧ternit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>aeternitas</ets>, fr.
<ets>aeternus</ets>. See <er>Etern</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Infinite duration, without beginning in the past or end in the
future; also, duration without end in the future; endless
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The high and lofty One, that inhabiteth <qex>eternity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Is. lvii. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Condition which begins at death;
immortality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou know'st 't is common; all that lives must die,⟦br⟧
Passing through nature to <qex>eternity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eternization</ent>⟦br⟧
